# ONNX Runtime

ONNX Runtime is a cross-platform inference and training machine-learning accelerator.

## Usage

```cpp
#include <onnxruntime_cxx_api.h>

// Create environment
Ort::Env env(ORT_LOGGING_LEVEL_WARNING, "MyApp");

// Create session options
Ort::SessionOptions session_options;
session_options.SetIntraOpNumThreads(1);

// Load model
Ort::Session session(env, "model.onnx", session_options);

// Get input/output info
auto input_name = session.GetInputNameAllocated(0);
auto output_name = session.GetOutputNameAllocated(0);

// Run inference
auto output_tensors = session.Run(
    Ort::RunOptions{nullptr},
    input_names.data(),
    input_tensors.data(),
    num_inputs,
    output_names.data(),
    num_outputs
);
```

## CMake Integration

```cmake
find_package(ONNXRuntime REQUIRED)
target_link_libraries(your_target PRIVATE onnxruntime::onnxruntime)
```

## Features

- **CUDA**: Enable with `onnxruntime[cuda]` for GPU acceleration
- **TensorRT**: Enable with `onnxruntime[tensorrt]` for NVIDIA TensorRT
- **DirectML**: Enable with `onnxruntime[directml]` for Windows DirectML

## Notes

- Default build is CPU-only static library
- For CUDA support, ensure CUDA and cuDNN are installed
- Model files (.onnx) must be provided separately
